# User guide documentation

When you **build, change, or remove** a user-facing feature in Directory Maps, update **`docs/USER_GUIDE.md`** in the same task.

## What to update

- **New feature** — Add or extend a section with steps a client user would follow (routes, buttons, prerequisites).
- **Changed behaviour** — Revise the affected section; remove outdated steps.
- **Removed feature** — Delete or shorten the section; note deprecation if beta users need it.

Also update when relevant:

- **`docs/FEATURES.md`** — Inventory, maturity, or route reference.
- **`docs/README.md`** — Only if the doc index or quick links change.

## Style

- Write for **client users**, not developers (no file paths in USER_GUIDE unless troubleshooting).
- Use the app’s real labels and hash routes (e.g. `/#/client/team`).
- Keep the **Quick reference** table at the bottom current.

## Do not

- Skip USER_GUIDE updates because the change “seems small.”
- Put implementation detail in USER_GUIDE (that belongs in FEATURES.md or specialist docs).
